How will you resolve bean ambiguity?
====================================
bean ambiguity means if one interface having 2 implementation if try to use @Autowired on interface our application will not run,it will give an error called ,required single bean,but found 2.
so have one annotation called @Qualifier()


1st Way
------

public class MailController{

  @Autowired
  @Qualifier("resendMailServiceImpl") //camelCaseNaming convesion 
  public MailService mailService;

}

public interface MailService{
}

@Service
public class ResendMailServiceImpl implements MailService{
}

 @Service
 public class SendGridMailServiceImpl implements MailService{
}

2nd Way
------

public class MailController{

  @Autowired
  @Qualifier("sendgrid-service") //service name
  public MailService mailService;

}

public interface MailService{
}

@Service("resend-service")
public class ResendMailServiceImpl implements MailService{
}

 @Service("sendgrid-service")
 public class SendGridMailServiceImpl implements MailService{
}


